HEADWORD: Mucivore
<hw>Mu"ci*vore</hw> <pr>(m⟦umac⟧"s⟦icr⟧*v⟦omac⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>mucus</ets> slime, mucus + <ets>vorare</ets> to
devour.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An insect which feeds on mucus,
or the sap of plants, as certain Diptera, of the tribe
<fam>Mucivora</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

